================================================================================
4. DATA HANDLING
================================================================================

Arctisoft Studio Hub uses a shared account system across all managed
applications. Only minimal data is stored on the server, while all
preferences and application data remain local on your device.

WHAT THE HUB STORES ON THE SERVER:

  - Account: Email, username, avatar and authentication credentials
  - Progress: Experience points and level
  - Licenses: License keys, activation status and device identifiers
  - Purchases: Transaction records and payment references

WHAT THE HUB STORES LOCALLY:

  - Session: Encrypted authentication tokens shared across applications
  - Settings: Application preferences and configuration
  - Cache: Release information, dashboard data and library state

WHAT THE HUB DOES NOT STORE:

  - Payment information (handled securely by Stripe)
  - Telemetry, analytics or behavioral tracking data
  - File system activity outside of managed application directories
  - Content processed by managed applications

PRIVACY CONTROLS:

You have control over your data:

  - Clear application cache via Help page tools
  - Sign out from all sessions via Settings
  - Delete your account and all associated data via Settings

DATA RETENTION:

  - Basic accounts: Automatically deleted after 365 days of inactivity
  - Premium accounts: Retained while any license is active

